Data on morphological variation in these mites are scattered in some papers concerning the taxonomy on this group ( Akyol 2011 ;
Doğan et al . 2015a
, b , 2016;
Dilkaraoğlu et al . 2016a
, b ; Bingül & Doğan 2017; Bingül et al . 2017; Koç & Poyraz Tınartaş 2017 ). They mentioned some asymmetries and numerical variations on genitals, aggenitals, some dorsal and ventral body setae, and differences in length and shape of some body setae in the Stigmaeidae . One minor asymmetric morphological variation in this species is noted: ag 1 is not situated on the same shield as the others on right side. This observed character variation, occurring only on one side, may be considered as a bilateral asymmetric anomaly.
